rComments: She's super knowledgeable, and has lots of real-life examples to use. She's always available to help. She speaks really fast, but repeats often and is happy to answer questions. If you're in to get easy credits, don't!

She's ok, speaks very fast though, it's hard to keep up. She says things that are not in her slides and will be in the online assignments. Also, she kept talking about her french class (which was unnecessary) and often forgot to translate her french slides from french to english. However, she seems to like what she does, which is good.
